Few notes on below code:

1. Syntactically zero-delay task call inside final block just compiles - I was hoping to get a warning
2. Call to t() in final block does NOT seem to execute 

```log
m From initial block
m.t
m                   10
```
I didn't see the m.t display from final() block call.

```verilog
module m;

  task t;
    $display ("%m");
  endtask : t

  initial begin
    $display ("%m From initial block");
    t();
    #10;
    $display ("%m ", $time);
    $finish(1);
  end

  final begin
    t();
    $display ("%m From final block");
  end
endmodule 

```

